HEADWORD: Hydroxyl
<hw>Hy*drox"yl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>,
2 + <ets>ox</ets>ygen + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
compound radical, or unsaturated group, <chform>HO</chform>, consisting
of one atom of hydrogen and one of oxygen. It is a characteristic part
of the hydrates, the alcohols, the oxygen acids, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

